 this approach is its focus on the coexistence of different forms of sociality in different strata of society.  aIssued also in print.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn German.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 01. Dez 2022) 4aAufsatzsammlung. 4aGeschichte 1750-1820. 4aGeselligkeit. 4aNordwestdeutschland. 70(DE-588)4035436-20(DE-627)1062476970(DE-576)209012676aLesegesellschaft2gnd 70(DE-588)4122925-30(DE-627)1057588920(DE-576)209555386aBildungsbürgertum2gnd 70(DE-588)4136030-80(DE-627)1056606200(DE-576)209665734aGeselligkeit2gnd 70(DE-588)4178965-90(DE-627)1053373740(DE-576)209988061aSalon2gnd 7aHISTORY / General.2bisacsh1 aAlbrecht, Peter, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aAlbrecht, Peter, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aBirtsch, Günter, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBrandes, Helga, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBödeker, Hans Erich, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBödeker, Hans Erich, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aBöning, Holger, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aEbeling, Hans-Heinrich, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aFehn, Ernst-Otto, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aGötz, Carmen, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHaug, Christine, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHerz, Andreas, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHinrichs, Emst, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHinrichs, Ernst, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHinrichs, Ernst, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabu